title: For Sale:  Shoot To Win A Mosin Nagant AND A 'Bring Your Own Shoot Off' ~ you DON'T want to miss this one!
location: Camdenton-Linn Creek. A Road, Missouri, United States
postcontent:
1 EVENT 2 SHOOT OFF COMPETITIONS!! WIN A 1953.9 TYPE 53 CARBINE and BRING YOUR PERSONAL RIFLE & OUT SHOOT EVERYONE ELSE FOR 50% OF THE ENTRY FEE!

Details of both are below:

SHOOT #3
Saturday July 6th join us for the 3rd Linn Creek Military Surplus Shoot Off. Starts at 12 noon sharp!

You will have a chance to win a first year 1953.9 (Made September of 1953) Type 53 Mosin Nagant Carbine (7.62x54r) donated by Anna W the winner of out first 2 events. No worries folks, she's removed herself from this shoot off 'so everyone else has a chance'...lol.

The shoot off general rules/info:

EAR PROTECTION IS MANDATORY! NO EXCEPTIONS!

The cost is $20 for each ticket entry or 3 for $50. Enter as many times as you like or can afford...lol. You may pay cash at the time of the shoot off or pre-pay via Pay Pal. Email me through this site with your desired number of entries and I will invoice you through pay pal. Credit cards accepted. If you pre-pay, please print off your payment page/receipt and bring it with you to the shoot. This is what will get your tickets in hand.

"What do we shoot for the event?" 
Everyone shoots the same rifle.... The prize you are trying to win. In this case an 1953.9 Mosin Nagant carbine. 

"How does it work?"

It's very simple. after everyone has paid & gotten their tickets, shooting order will be a random draw.

You shoot 5 rounds at 50 yards, open sights with ammo that I provide. Military surplus ammo straight from the spam can. In this case 188 gr Bulgarian surplus ammo.

No practice shots with the prize rifle. You go in cold just like everyone else. 

You can sit at the bench (no shooting rests, props or whatever, just the sling & your arms), sitting, prone or open hand as you so choose. This is an informal shoot, so please, no hardcore rule umpires, we want to keep it casual & easy going. In event of a tie there will be a 1 shot 'shoot off'. In the event of any disagreements/disputes, my judgement is final. 

We will spot and show you where your rounds are landing. 

Best points score takes the rifle home. It's that simple. Shoot 5 rounds, get the high score & take the rifle home with you. 

Obviously, you must be present to win. 
*******************************************************************
***************BRING YOUR OWN RIFLE & SHOOT TO WIN**************
*******************************************************************

It's pretty simple. 

$5 gets you in. Bring 5 rounds of your own ammo, shoot it out of your gun at 200 yards. High score wins.

Any caliber rifle, scoped or not at your preference. At the bench, off hand, sitting or prone. Your choice, no rests or bi pods. 

As reported to me by a few friends that are attending, there are .22's, .243, 30/30 and POSSIBLY a .50 Cal Barrett being entered...lol. (IDK if blowing up the target will win, but it'll sure be fun to watch...lol.)

Do you have a nail driver? Bring it, show off your chops & take a few bucks home along with the bragging rights!

Highest score with 5 rounds will win you 1/2 (50%) of the entry fees to the 'bring your own' shoot. 

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Feel free to bring a few weapons/accessories to trade and or show off. After the shoot off it will be open range time for anyone wanting to shoot. There is a 300 yd range, pistol and shotgun pits as well. 

The range is in Linn Creek on A Rd. Located between Camdenton and Osage Beach. After you are on A rd. you will travel about 4 1/2 miles to Garrison. It will be a right turn, the only way you can go. Follow the gravel rd to the bottom of the hill & just across the low water bridge you will see Centerpoint gun club on the right. That is where we will be meeting for the shoot.

https://maps.google.com/maps?q=linn+creek+mo&ie=UTF-8&hq&hnear=0x87c4dc08eb4b5a71%3A0x1e71c7b79eb3348c%2CLinn+Creek%2C+MO&gl=us&ei=7ppnUav-OsvkqQHJ3YDQDg&ved=0CJwBELYD

If you have any questions or comments, please feel free to reply on the Shoot Off page or call me on my cell at REDACTED

My direct email is REDACTED

Linn Creek Milsurp Shoot Off group page on Facebook. Please feel free to join our FB group for updates, pics of our first 2 shoots and more. 
https://www.facebook.com/groups/REDACTED77918/

If for nothing else, you should come by for the 'Grand Volley' when all is said & done.

https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=REDACTED89204&set=o.REDACTED77918&type=2&theater

There is no age limit, if you can handle & fire the weapon safely, your welcome to come and play with us. 

The winner from our first and 2nd shoot Anna. (a delightful 20 yr old young lady) out shot 9 and 15 guys respectively & took home a very nice 1943 Mosin Nagant with all matching numbers and accessories from the first and a sweet 1956 Type 53 in an ATI stock the second time around.

This is a primitive site. You will need to bring lawn chairs/something to sit on. Water isn't a bad idea. I'll have some there for everyone, but extra never hurts. A canopy/umbrella if you want shade. I'll have an awning & an umbrella, but we can always use more. 

This is a family event & is a LOT of fun with like minded folk. Come on down, meet new friends and enjoy a beautiful summer day in the Ozarks. 

PS: there is a creek near by (100yds or less) if you want to really cool off.

title: For Sale:  Shoot To Win A Mosin Nagant AND A 'Bring Your Own Shoot Off' ~ you DON'T want to miss this one!
location: Camdenton-Linn Creek. A Road, Missouri, United States
postcontent:
1 EVENT 2 SHOOT OFF COMPETITIONS!! WIN A 1953.9 TYPE 53 CARBINE and BRING YOUR PERSONAL RIFLE & OUT SHOOT EVERYONE ELSE FOR 50% OF THE ENTRY FEE!

Details of both are below:

SHOOT #3
Saturday July 6th join us for the 3rd Linn Creek Military Surplus Shoot Off. Starts at 12 noon sharp!

You will have a chance to win a first year 1953.9 (Made September of 1953) Type 53 Mosin Nagant Carbine (7.62x54r) donated by Anna W the winner of out first 2 events. No worries folks, she's removed herself from this shoot off 'so everyone else has a chance'...lol.

The shoot off general rules/info:

EAR PROTECTION IS MANDATORY! NO EXCEPTIONS!

The cost is $20 for each ticket entry or 3 for $50. Enter as many times as you like or can afford...lol. You may pay cash at the time of the shoot off or pre-pay via Pay Pal. Email me through this site with your desired number of entries and I will invoice you through pay pal. Credit cards accepted. If you pre-pay, please print off your payment page/receipt and bring it with you to the shoot. This is what will get your tickets in hand.

"What do we shoot for the event?" 
Everyone shoots the same rifle.... The prize you are trying to win. In this case an 1953.9 Mosin Nagant carbine. 

"How does it work?"

It's very simple. after everyone has paid & gotten their tickets, shooting order will be a random draw.

You shoot 5 rounds at 50 yards, open sights with ammo that I provide. Military surplus ammo straight from the spam can. In this case 188 gr Bulgarian surplus ammo.

No practice shots with the prize rifle. You go in cold just like everyone else. 

You can sit at the bench (no shooting rests, props or whatever, just the sling & your arms), sitting, prone or open hand as you so choose. This is an informal shoot, so please, no hardcore rule umpires, we want to keep it casual & easy going. In event of a tie there will be a 1 shot 'shoot off'. In the event of any disagreements/disputes, my judgement is final. 

We will spot and show you where your rounds are landing. 

Best points score takes the rifle home. It's that simple. Shoot 5 rounds, get the high score & take the rifle home with you. 

Obviously, you must be present to win. 
*******************************************************************
***************BRING YOUR OWN RIFLE & SHOOT TO WIN**************
*******************************************************************

It's pretty simple. 

$5 gets you in. Bring 5 rounds of your own ammo, shoot it out of your gun at 200 yards. High score wins.

Any caliber rifle, scoped or not at your preference. At the bench, off hand, sitting or prone. Your choice, no rests or bi pods. 

As reported to me by a few friends that are attending, there are .22's, .243, 30/30 and POSSIBLY a .50 Cal Barrett being entered...lol. (IDK if blowing up the target will win, but it'll sure be fun to watch...lol.)

Do you have a nail driver? Bring it, show off your chops & take a few bucks home along with the bragging rights!

Highest score with 5 rounds will win you 1/2 (50%) of the entry fees to the 'bring your own' shoot. 

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Feel free to bring a few weapons/accessories to trade and or show off. After the shoot off it will be open range time for anyone wanting to shoot. There is a 300 yd range, pistol and shotgun pits as well. 

The range is in Linn Creek on A Rd. Located between Camdenton and Osage Beach. After you are on A rd. you will travel about 4 1/2 miles to Garrison. It will be a right turn, the only way you can go. Follow the gravel rd to the bottom of the hill & just across the low water bridge you will see Centerpoint gun club on the right. That is where we will be meeting for the shoot.

https://maps.google.com/maps?q=linn+creek+mo&ie=UTF-8&hq&hnear=0x87c4dc08eb4b5a71%3A0x1e71c7b79eb3348c%2CLinn+Creek%2C+MO&gl=us&ei=7ppnUav-OsvkqQHJ3YDQDg&ved=0CJwBELYD

If you have any questions or comments, please feel free to reply on the Shoot Off page or call me on my cell at 573 286 4090

My direct email is vintagedelights01@gmail.com

Linn Creek Milsurp Shoot Off group page on Facebook. Please feel free to join our FB group for updates, pics of our first 2 shoots and more. 
https://www.facebook.com/groups/159547780877918/

If for nothing else, you should come by for the 'Grand Volley' when all is said & done.

https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=274895375989204&set=o.159547780877918&type=2&theater

There is no age limit, if you can handle & fire the weapon safely, your welcome to come and play with us. 

The winner from our first and 2nd shoot Anna. (a delightful 20 yr old young lady) out shot 9 and 15 guys respectively & took home a very nice 1943 Mosin Nagant with all matching numbers and accessories from the first and a sweet 1956 Type 53 in an ATI stock the second time around.

This is a primitive site. You will need to bring lawn chairs/something to sit on. Water isn't a bad idea. I'll have some there for everyone, but extra never hurts. A canopy/umbrella if you want shade. I'll have an awning & an umbrella, but we can always use more. 

This is a family event & is a LOT of fun with like minded folk. Come on down, meet new friends and enjoy a beautiful summer day in the Ozarks. 

PS: there is a creek near by (100yds or less) if you want to really cool off.

We have shooters from all over the state coming in for the event. St. Louis, St. Joseph, Kansas City, Joplin, Springfield and all points in between. It's worth the drive folks, trust me on this one.

This is a very nice unfired .308/7.62 Nato AR-10 style rifle meant to replace the Remington M24 sniper rifle. The sniper choice of summited rifles Was the Remington XM110 because of it's reliability. NEW DYNAMIC PISTOL DIES
Dillon's New Dynamic Pistol dies allow you to easily clean the seating and crimp dies, and even change the bullet seating stem from round nose to semi-wad cutter in seconds - all without removing the die body from your reloading press. 

Sizing/Depriming Die 
Our sizing/depriming dies feature a unique "floating decap assembly" with a snap spring that throws the spent primer off the pin and eliminates the problem of primer "draw back" that often occurs when decapping military brass. The primary feature of Dillon's size die design the long, tapered carbide ring with a radiused opening remains unchanged. 
That radiused opening, and its importance to progressive reloading, is one of the reasons why our seat and crimp dies are better. We found a way of manufacturing these dies that have enabled us to make the lead-in radius even bigger! The bigger radius makes progressive loading even smoother .

Bullet Seating Die 
Our new quick-disassembly seat die allows the user to disassemble and clean the seat die without losing adjustment. In this manner, bullet lube and shavings can be quickly removed from the die, thereby guaranteeing a constant seating depth. We've incorporated a "flip-flop" seating stem and a clip that enables you to remove the die insert and change the seating stem from round nose to semi-wadcutter without unscrewing a seating stem out of the die body. We've always included both types of seating stems, but the new double-ended design makes it a simple matter to remove a pin, reverse the seating stem, make any minor seating depth adjustments that may be necessary and go on loading in a fraction of the time it used to take. 

Crimp Die 
We've made it easy for you to remove the die insert for cleaning without having to change the critical crimp adjustment. Once your crimp die is set for the proper amount of crimp, you'll never have to change it. This is especially good news for all of you who load lead bullets! Before, you had to unscrew the die from the toolhead and disassemble the die in order to remove any bullet lube or lead residue. Then, you had to start from square one to re-adjust the crimp. Those days are over. All you have to do now is pop a clip and the die insert drops into your hand for cleaning.
